      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/37/18",
      "text": [
        ": «اِذْهَبْ فَأَعْطِ عَنْ عِيَالِنَا اَلْفِطْرَةَ وَ عَنِ اَلرَّقِيقِ وَ اِجْمَعْهُمْ وَ لاَ تَدَعْ مِنْهُمْ أَحَداً فَإِنَّكَ إِنْ تَرَكْتَ مِنْهُمْ إِنْسَاناً تَخَوَّفْتُ عَلَيْهِ اَلْفَوْتَ» قُلْتُ وَ مَا اَلْفَوْتُ قَالَ «اَلْمَوْتُ»."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2078 - It is narrated from Ishaq ibn Ammar, from Mu’attib, who said:\nAbu Abdullah (as) said:\n\"Go and give Zakat al-Fitr on behalf of our household and for the servants. Include all of them and do not leave anyone out. If you leave out even one person, I fear for them the 'fawt' (loss).\"\nI asked: \"What is 'fawt'?\"\nImam (as) replied: \"Death.\""
        ]
      }
    },
